<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 2:55PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Lucas County through
345 PM EDT...
At 255 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Holland, or near Swanton, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Toledo, Swanton, Oregon, Sylvania, Holland, Maumee, Ottawa Hills,
Berkey, Harbor View, Reno Beach and Bono.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
northwestern Ohio.</instruction>
